He took the crowbar from him and
said, what is that, your

00:00:45.600 --> 00:00:47.391
off switch?

00:00:47.391 --> 00:00:49.370
And two North Koreans
came back.

00:00:49.370 --> 00:00:52.150
Now they're giving
Mr. Kim shit.

00:00:52.150 --> 00:00:54.190
And they're quite angry.

00:00:54.190 --> 00:00:58.050
So we're probably going to
have to get out of here.

00:00:58.050 --> 00:00:59.300
MALE SPEAKER 1:
[SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:01:04.920 --> 00:01:07.030
SHANE SMITH: And so, oh shit,
here comes another truck.

00:01:07.030 --> 00:01:08.190
Now we're surrounded.

00:01:08.190 --> 00:01:09.260
They're got a truck up there.

00:01:09.260 --> 00:01:12.050
They've got a truck
behind here.

00:01:12.050 --> 00:01:12.850
What'd he say?

00:01:12.850 --> 00:01:14.505
SIMON OSTROVSKY: He said he
came to tell us that he

00:01:14.505 --> 00:01:17.070
doesn't want us filming anymore,
and he's come to

00:01:17.070 --> 00:01:18.550
block the road.

00:01:18.550 --> 00:01:19.800
SHANE SMITH: Really?

00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:28.100
All right.

00:01:28.100 --> 00:01:29.800
Well, let's go find
another crew.

00:01:29.800 --> 00:01:31.290
Let's go.

00:01:31.290 --> 00:01:32.675
The Fish is the boss.

00:01:35.900 --> 00:01:38.030
As the Fish took us further
into the forest on these

00:01:38.030 --> 00:01:40.570
rutted dirt tracks, the
atmosphere in the truck got a

00:01:40.570 --> 00:01:43.430
little bit goofy because of
the lunacy that was being

00:01:43.430 --> 00:01:46.580
played out in the oddest game
of low-grade cat and mouse

00:01:46.580 --> 00:01:47.490
I've ever seen.

00:01:47.490 --> 00:01:50.950
Ask about how we get home.

00:01:50.950 --> 00:01:54.400
We're in a high-speed car chase
at five miles an hour

00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:57.566
through the wilds of Siberia.

00:01:57.566 --> 00:01:59.990
They're stopping, we go to
try to pass them, and

00:01:59.990 --> 00:02:00.950
then they speed up.

00:02:00.950 --> 00:02:03.320
We sort of go on a side road,
and then they head

00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:04.520
us off at the pass.

00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:07.870
It's a game of chicken out
in the middle of nowhere.

00:02:07.870 --> 00:02:09.120
IGOR "THE FISH" RYBAKOV:
[SPEAKING RUSSIAN]

00:02:15.742 --> 00:02:16.734
SIMON OSTROVSKY: He was
just telling us.

00:02:16.734 --> 00:02:17.726
KIM YUN ZUN: [SPEAKING RUSSIAN]

00:02:17.726 --> 00:02:18.718
IGOR "THE FISH" RYBAKOV:
[SPEAKING RUSSIAN]

00:02:18.718 --> 00:02:20.450
SIMON OSTROVSKY: He says he's
on their blacklist.

00:02:20.450 --> 00:02:22.850
SHANE SMITH: The Fish seemed
tired of this game and

00:02:22.850 --> 00:02:25.760
suggested we pull over for some
lunch, which consisted of

00:02:25.760 --> 00:02:29.240
paprika chips, bread, vodka,
and a shotgun.

00:02:31.915 --> 00:02:32.860
IGOR "THE FISH" RYBAKOV:
[SPEAKING RUSSIAN], cowboy.

00:02:32.860 --> 00:02:33.435
SHANE SMITH: Cowboy.

00:02:33.435 --> 00:02:34.685
SIMON OSTROVSKY: Cowboy.

00:02:42.227 --> 00:02:44.470
SHANE SMITH: The North Koreans
are going-- what the fuck kind

00:02:44.470 --> 00:02:46.530
of journalists are these?

00:02:46.530 --> 00:02:47.820
Well, we found our
North Koreans.

00:02:47.820 --> 00:02:52.200
Now let's get wasted and shoot
off guns with the mafia.

00:02:52.200 --> 00:02:54.860
I hit it, but I didn't
break it.

00:02:54.860 --> 00:02:56.660
[APPLAUSE]

00:02:56.660 --> 00:02:57.710
SHANE SMITH: It turned
out there was method

00:02:57.710 --> 00:02:58.940
in the Fish's madness.

00:02:58.940 --> 00:03:01.410
Because our lunchtime shooting
party seemed to have cowed the

00:03:01.410 --> 00:03:04.020
North Koreans just enough to get
us out of the wilderness,

00:03:04.020 --> 00:03:07.030
which was very good because
the all-menacing Siberian

00:03:07.030 --> 00:03:10.570
darkness was fast approaching.

00:03:10.570 --> 00:03:13.220
When we finally got to town,
they, of course,

00:03:13.220 --> 00:03:14.190
were waiting for us.

00:03:14.190 --> 00:03:16.740
And the North Korean security
dude just showed up.

00:03:16.740 --> 00:03:18.020
And he won't leave us alone.

00:03:18.020 --> 00:03:19.150
And he's just standing
there trying

00:03:19.150 --> 00:03:20.710
to look at our passports.

00:03:20.710 --> 00:03:23.250
And trying to see all
of our stuff.

00:03:23.250 --> 00:03:24.360
He's trying to be scary.

00:03:24.360 --> 00:03:25.704
SIMON OSTROVSKY:
[SPEAKING RUSSIAN]

00:03:25.704 --> 00:03:28.690
