00:03:28.690 --> 00:03:30.050
SHANE SMITH: And when we got
on the train and said our

00:03:30.050 --> 00:03:32.710
teary goodbyes to the Fish, we
realized that half the one-car

00:03:32.710 --> 00:03:36.390
train was our crew, and the
other half were North Koreans.

00:03:36.390 --> 00:03:37.540
[SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:03:37.540 --> 00:03:39.120
SIMON OSTROVSKY: That was
the captain of the camp.

00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:39.930
SHANE SMITH: Great.

00:03:39.930 --> 00:03:42.740
So we locked ourselves into our
compartment and spent the

00:03:42.740 --> 00:03:45.130
night backing up our hard drives
and hiding all of our

00:03:45.130 --> 00:03:48.390
footage, which turned out be
wise because we were met back

00:03:48.390 --> 00:03:51.830
in Tynda by the FSB, the local
militia, the North Koreans,

00:03:51.830 --> 00:03:54.030
and some plainclothes detectives
who promptly

00:03:54.030 --> 00:03:54.980
detained us.

00:03:54.980 --> 00:03:56.510
So they asked us a
lot of questions.

00:03:56.510 --> 00:03:58.910
And they kept asking us
about the pipeline.

00:03:58.910 --> 00:04:00.185
Are you here to shoot
the pipeline?

00:04:00.185 --> 00:04:01.340
Are you here to shoot
the pipeline?

00:04:01.340 --> 00:04:02.500
We were like, we don't know
anything about a pipeline.

00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:04.440
We're here to shoot
North Koreans.

00:04:04.440 --> 00:04:07.010
They knew about the Russian cop
who had taken us to the

00:04:07.010 --> 00:04:07.700
North Korean camp.

00:04:07.700 --> 00:04:09.620
They knew about the chief
of police in the north.

00:04:09.620 --> 00:04:13.550
Simon refused to be intimidated,
and he said, if

00:04:13.550 --> 00:04:15.430
you want to ask any questions,
ask me here.

00:04:15.430 --> 00:04:16.339
I'm not going with you.

00:04:16.339 --> 00:04:17.690
I'm not going away with you.

00:04:17.690 --> 00:04:18.850
They finally let us go.

00:04:18.850 --> 00:04:20.600
We freaked out a little
bit, grabbed our

00:04:20.600 --> 00:04:22.089
stuff, and took off.

00:04:22.089 --> 00:04:24.320
We quickly hired a car
and made a break

00:04:24.320 --> 00:04:25.480
for the Chinese border.

00:04:25.480 --> 00:04:28.110
When we finally got to the
border, we realized that part

00:04:28.110 --> 00:04:30.080
of the reason for all this panic
and fear on the North

00:04:30.080 --> 00:04:33.260
Korean and Russian side was that
Kim Jong-Il, who almost

00:04:33.260 --> 00:04:35.910
never leaves North Korea, had
secretly come to the same

00:04:35.910 --> 00:04:39.400
place we were, the Amur region
of Russia, coincidentally at

00:04:39.400 --> 00:04:42.200
the exact same time we were
there to hold talks with

00:04:42.200 --> 00:04:45.210
President Medvedev about more
trade and labor agreements

00:04:45.210 --> 00:04:47.660
between the two countries.

00:04:47.660 --> 00:04:50.770
So this means that, while we
were there, the Great Leader

00:04:50.770 --> 00:04:53.780
was selling even more of his
people off, so he could make

00:04:53.780 --> 00:04:57.680
even more money, so you could
make more weapons, so he could

00:04:57.680 --> 00:05:01.110
extort more food and aid and
supplies from America and

00:05:01.110 --> 00:05:04.020
Japan, who he's technically
still at war with.

00:05:10.340 --> 00:05:14.130
And this, better than almost
anything I could think of,

00:05:14.130 --> 00:05:17.080
sums up the lunacy of
the modern world.

00:05:17.080 --> 00:05:18.520
Thank you and goodnight.

